  "questions": [
    {
      "text": "A 69-year-old man comes to the physician because of a 3-week history of constant dull pain in both flanks. The pain is unrelated to movement or food intake. Over the past 2 weeks, he has also had fatigue, loss of appetite, nausea, and a slightly decreased urine output. He reports no dysuria or urinary urgency. He has a long history of cluster headaches that respond well to oral ergotamine, which he has been taking for many years to treat acute attacks. He has smoked one pack of cigarettes daily for the past 25 years. His blood pressure is 152/98 mm Hg. Physical examination shows bilateral pitting edema of the ankles. Abdominal and pelvic examination, including a digital rectal examination, show no abnormalities. Urinalysis shows no abnormalities. Renal ultrasonography shows bilateral dilatation of the renal pelvis, calyces, and proximal ureter. Which of the following is the most likely cause of this patient's ultrasound findings?",
      "choices": [
        {
          "id": 1,
          "text": "Bladder cancer"
        },
        {
          "id": 2,
          "text": "Ureteropelvic junction obstruction"
        },
        {
          "id": 3,
          "text": "Retroperitoneal fibrosis"
        },
        {
          "id": 4,
          "text": "Nephrolithiasis"
        },
        {
          "id": 5,
          "text": "Benign prostatic hyperplasia"
        }
      ],
      "correct_choice_id": 3,
      "solution": "<div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>A) INCORRECT:</h4>\n<a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=6i0jsf&anker=Z1bd4f0f15ab6e834e41a13955a1ec451\" data-learningcard-id=\"6i0jsf\" data-anker=\"Z1bd4f0f15ab6e834e41a13955a1ec451\" data-section-id=\"nBa7YM\" data-sememe-id=\"NSb--G\">Bladder cancer</a>, which this patient is at increased risk for because of his age and history of smoking, can lead to <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Ni0-7f&anker=Zc73fc3dea6689aacbf97773ad1038288\" data-learningcard-id=\"Ni0-7f\" data-anker=\"Zc73fc3dea6689aacbf97773ad1038288\" data-sememe-id=\"vl0AAT\">urinary tract obstruction</a> and subsequent bilateral <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Ni0-7f&anker=Zf87cb8cc29c1c742e9f14924ec88bd7e\" data-learningcard-id=\"Ni0-7f\" data-anker=\"Zf87cb8cc29c1c742e9f14924ec88bd7e\" data-section-id=\"tCaXF5\" data-sememe-id=\"QLYuxp\">hydronephrosis</a>. However, <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Ni0-7f&anker=Zc73fc3dea6689aacbf97773ad1038288\" data-learningcard-id=\"Ni0-7f\" data-anker=\"Zc73fc3dea6689aacbf97773ad1038288\" data-sememe-id=\"vl0AAT\">urinary tract obstruction</a> and <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=xN0EWg&anker=Zd673a3f7ee36023aab5a267899e984cc\" data-learningcard-id=\"xN0EWg\" data-anker=\"Zd673a3f7ee36023aab5a267899e984cc\" data-section-id=\"NBX-a00\">pain</a> are only expected in advanced and <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=WM0Png&anker=Z56ce78424b29da57669d773285a33fa6\" data-learningcard-id=\"WM0Png\" data-anker=\"Z56ce78424b29da57669d773285a33fa6\" data-section-id=\"XzX9r00\" data-sememe-id=\"IrXYiz\">metastatic</a> disease; <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Wq0PxS&anker=Z8be00655e698d66639db574074c169a2\" data-learningcard-id=\"Wq0PxS\" data-anker=\"Z8be00655e698d66639db574074c169a2\" data-section-id=\"5W1iNf0\" data-sememe-id=\"1g0282\">gross hematuria</a> and/or irritative voiding symptoms (e.g., <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Ku0UH3&anker=Z4f41e78ad20decca22732c8ea55bc4cb\" data-learningcard-id=\"Ku0UH3\" data-anker=\"Z4f41e78ad20decca22732c8ea55bc4cb\" data-sememe-id=\"aT0Q62\">dysuria</a>, <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=kg0mv2&anker=Z4696f8e500da3c30710da62453f005f8\" data-learningcard-id=\"kg0mv2\" data-anker=\"Z4696f8e500da3c30710da62453f005f8\" data-section-id=\"iJXJF_\" data-sememe-id=\"hfbcNG\">urinary frequency</a>, <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=yi0d8f&anker=Z3c98e5f5727b8a9612e97d548843b52b\" data-learningcard-id=\"yi0d8f\" data-anker=\"Z3c98e5f5727b8a9612e97d548843b52b\" data-section-id=\"K-aUyM\" data-sememe-id=\"Lbaw8Q\">urinary urgency</a>) are more common initial manifestations. Furthermore, this patient's history of <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Zm0ZVg&anker=Z1d819c586b99b3cfa1ca4945633fbbe8\" data-learningcard-id=\"Zm0ZVg\" data-anker=\"Z1d819c586b99b3cfa1ca4945633fbbe8\" data-section-id=\"VsbGFE\" data-sememe-id=\"FjagXk\">ergot</a> alkaloid intake makes another cause more likely.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>B) INCORRECT:</h4>\n<a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Ni0-7f&anker=Z7583ee52329e30843b744ec3e7f4c96f\" data-learningcard-id=\"Ni0-7f\" data-anker=\"Z7583ee52329e30843b744ec3e7f4c96f\" data-section-id=\"FCagF5\" data-sememe-id=\"hLYcxp\">Ureteropelvic junction (UPJ) obstruction</a> can manifest with <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Ni0-7f&anker=Zf87cb8cc29c1c742e9f14924ec88bd7e\" data-learningcard-id=\"Ni0-7f\" data-anker=\"Zf87cb8cc29c1c742e9f14924ec88bd7e\" data-section-id=\"tCaXF5\" data-sememe-id=\"QLYuxp\">hydronephrosis</a>. However, <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Ni0-7f&anker=Z7583ee52329e30843b744ec3e7f4c96f\" data-learningcard-id=\"Ni0-7f\" data-anker=\"Z7583ee52329e30843b744ec3e7f4c96f\" data-section-id=\"FCagF5\" data-sememe-id=\"hLYcxp\">UPJ obstruction</a> occurs at the junction of the <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=m60VlS&anker=Zd75b42544ea7bde39ebe548ac34075d6\" data-learningcard-id=\"m60VlS\" data-anker=\"Zd75b42544ea7bde39ebe548ac34075d6\" data-section-id=\"p8cLnV0\" data-sememe-id=\"SZcyaa0\">renal pelvis</a> and <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Rp0l6S&anker=Z0676a1c90d158f1984abc0e2fece9c54\" data-learningcard-id=\"Rp0l6S\" data-anker=\"Z0676a1c90d158f1984abc0e2fece9c54\" data-section-id=\"JwcsPe0\">ureter</a>, hence, the <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=xo0EVS&anker=Z3538c7d0d3c09a64652ecccc7971d5ae\" data-learningcard-id=\"xo0EVS\" data-anker=\"Z3538c7d0d3c09a64652ecccc7971d5ae\" data-section-id=\"h_ccLU0\">proximal</a> <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Rp0l6S&anker=Z0676a1c90d158f1984abc0e2fece9c54\" data-learningcard-id=\"Rp0l6S\" data-anker=\"Z0676a1c90d158f1984abc0e2fece9c54\" data-section-id=\"JwcsPe0\">ureter</a> would not be dilated. Moreover, <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Ni0-7f&anker=Z7583ee52329e30843b744ec3e7f4c96f\" data-learningcard-id=\"Ni0-7f\" data-anker=\"Z7583ee52329e30843b744ec3e7f4c96f\" data-section-id=\"FCagF5\" data-sememe-id=\"hLYcxp\">UPJ obstruction</a> is more commonly diagnosed in children and typically manifests with unilateral rather than bilateral <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Ni0-7f&anker=Zf87cb8cc29c1c742e9f14924ec88bd7e\" data-learningcard-id=\"Ni0-7f\" data-anker=\"Zf87cb8cc29c1c742e9f14924ec88bd7e\" data-section-id=\"tCaXF5\" data-sememe-id=\"QLYuxp\">hydronephrosis</a>.</div><div><h4 style='color: #34d399; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>C) CORRECT:</h4>\n<span class=\"wichtig\"><b><a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=9h0NTf&anker=Z03f0142bdc8116a585676a7b55dcd8cb\" data-learningcard-id=\"9h0NTf\" data-anker=\"Z03f0142bdc8116a585676a7b55dcd8cb\" data-sememe-id=\"0CYeqr\">Retroperitoneal fibrosis</a> </b></span>(<span data-sememe-id=\"t9cX6e0\">RPF</span>) is a rare disease characterized by inflammation and <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=ro0fWS&anker=Zf29b9e7e01bf75d0402e969b50992d30\" data-learningcard-id=\"ro0fWS\" data-anker=\"Zf29b9e7e01bf75d0402e969b50992d30\" data-section-id=\"H9cKKe0\" data-sememe-id=\"yi0d8f\">fibrosis</a> of the <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=LJ0wuS&anker=Z190eccffe0c6c2ad5707460bd343c295\" data-learningcard-id=\"LJ0wuS\" data-anker=\"Z190eccffe0c6c2ad5707460bd343c295\" data-section-id=\"qa1Cl20\" data-sememe-id=\"VJXGG_\">retroperitoneum</a> resulting in compression and <span class=\"wichtig\"><b>encasement of the <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Rp0l6S&anker=Z0676a1c90d158f1984abc0e2fece9c54\" data-learningcard-id=\"Rp0l6S\" data-anker=\"Z0676a1c90d158f1984abc0e2fece9c54\" data-section-id=\"JwcsPe0\">ureter</a></b></span> and/or the <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=LJ0wuS&anker=Z190eccffe0c6c2ad5707460bd343c295\" data-learningcard-id=\"LJ0wuS\" data-anker=\"Z190eccffe0c6c2ad5707460bd343c295\" data-section-id=\"qa1Cl20\" data-sememe-id=\"VJXGG_\">retroperitoneal</a> <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=ZK0ZUS&anker=Ze70cc99757e1ea860cd2529fb952e9f0\" data-learningcard-id=\"ZK0ZUS\" data-anker=\"Ze70cc99757e1ea860cd2529fb952e9f0\">blood vessels</a>. Patients typically present with <span data-sememe-id=\"STXyJx\">constitutional symptoms</span> and <span class=\"wichtig\"><b>constant dull flank <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=xN0EWg&anker=Zd673a3f7ee36023aab5a267899e984cc\" data-learningcard-id=\"xN0EWg\" data-anker=\"Zd673a3f7ee36023aab5a267899e984cc\" data-section-id=\"NBX-a00\">pain</a></b></span> that is unrelated to movement or food intake. Bilateral <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Ni0-7f&anker=Z4e3e1e2029b69cc6e4ac26790a2bc09e\" data-learningcard-id=\"Ni0-7f\" data-anker=\"Z4e3e1e2029b69cc6e4ac26790a2bc09e\" data-section-id=\"HCaKt5\">ureteral obstruction</a> with subsequent <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Ni0-7f&anker=Zf87cb8cc29c1c742e9f14924ec88bd7e\" data-learningcard-id=\"Ni0-7f\" data-anker=\"Zf87cb8cc29c1c742e9f14924ec88bd7e\" data-section-id=\"tCaXF5\" data-sememe-id=\"QLYuxp\">hydronephrosis</a> and <span class=\"wichtig\"><b><a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Ni0-7f&anker=Z65a6437c3b12d661bee8f833a8ae71b6\" data-learningcard-id=\"Ni0-7f\" data-anker=\"Z65a6437c3b12d661bee8f833a8ae71b6\" data-section-id=\"wCah85\" data-sememe-id=\"OLYIBp\">obstructive nephropathy</a></b></span>, as seen here, is common.<br><br><span data-sememe-id=\"t9cX6e0\">RPF</span> can be primary (most common) or secondary (e.g., drug-induced, inflammatory, <span data-sememe-id=\"Qh0udf\">iatrogenic</span>). Smoking and <span class=\"wichtig\"><b>chronic <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Zm0ZVg&anker=Z1d819c586b99b3cfa1ca4945633fbbe8\" data-learningcard-id=\"Zm0ZVg\" data-anker=\"Z1d819c586b99b3cfa1ca4945633fbbe8\" data-section-id=\"VsbGFE\" data-sememe-id=\"FjagXk\">ergot</a> alkaloid therapy </b></span>are important <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=ps0LDh&anker=Zbc0d0ff153bc5c7a27589815d0c842fd\" data-learningcard-id=\"ps0LDh\" data-anker=\"Zbc0d0ff153bc5c7a27589815d0c842fd\" data-section-id=\"FfWgLk0\" data-sememe-id=\"b31HSg0\">risk factors</a>, along with abdominal <span data-sememe-id=\"ta1Xm20\">irradiation</span>, <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=LJ0wuS&anker=Z190eccffe0c6c2ad5707460bd343c295\" data-learningcard-id=\"LJ0wuS\" data-anker=\"Z190eccffe0c6c2ad5707460bd343c295\" data-section-id=\"qa1Cl20\" data-sememe-id=\"VJXGG_\">retroperitoneal</a> surgeries, and <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Vu0GJ3&anker=Z6709f19b0cddb8847d2d6ffe04719c2b\" data-learningcard-id=\"Vu0GJ3\" data-anker=\"Z6709f19b0cddb8847d2d6ffe04719c2b\" data-sememe-id=\"pwcLPe0\">IgG4-related systemic disease</a>.<img src='https://media-us.amboss.com/media/thumbs/big_65e06b06036128.19499865.jpg' alt='Explanation Image' style='width: 100%; border-radius: 12px; margin-top: 16px;'><div style='margin-top: 16px; border-top: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.1); padding-top: 16px;'><h5 style='font-weight: bold; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.7); margin-bottom: 8px;'>Image Description:</h5><div style='font-size: 0.9em; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.9); line-height: 1.6;'><p>Excretory urogram (late phase)</p><p>Hydroureteronephrosis (green overlay) is seen proximal to medial deviation and tapering (arrows) of the mid third of the ureters.</p><p>This appearance is typical of retroperitoneal fibrosis. Several other diseases that also increase soft tissue near the ureters may cause medial ureteral deviation (e.g., lymphoma, extramedullary hematopoiesis, Erdheim-Chester disease), as may psoas muscle hypertrophy.<br/><br/>Outlines: Kidneys</p></div></div></div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>D) INCORRECT:</h4>\n<a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=qg0Cw2&anker=Z45c7ff4091f4118f9a1659cdec6c8bdd\" data-learningcard-id=\"qg0Cw2\" data-anker=\"Z45c7ff4091f4118f9a1659cdec6c8bdd\" data-sememe-id=\"T406iT\">Nephrolithiasis</a> can cause flank <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=xN0EWg&anker=Zd673a3f7ee36023aab5a267899e984cc\" data-learningcard-id=\"xN0EWg\" data-anker=\"Zd673a3f7ee36023aab5a267899e984cc\" data-section-id=\"NBX-a00\">pain</a>, <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=7J04vS&anker=Z2f0b48ef2acaab783b03e4c8d2404f90\" data-learningcard-id=\"7J04vS\" data-anker=\"Z2f0b48ef2acaab783b03e4c8d2404f90\">nausea</a>, and <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Ni0-7f&anker=Zab7cfff8ab860b5898e5793a9c031324\" data-learningcard-id=\"Ni0-7f\" data-anker=\"Zab7cfff8ab860b5898e5793a9c031324\" data-section-id=\"HCaKt5\" data-sememe-id=\"SLYyCp\">upper urinary tract obstruction</a>. However, obstruction is typically unilateral in <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=qg0Cw2&anker=Z45c7ff4091f4118f9a1659cdec6c8bdd\" data-learningcard-id=\"qg0Cw2\" data-anker=\"Z45c7ff4091f4118f9a1659cdec6c8bdd\" data-sememe-id=\"T406iT\">nephrolithiasis</a>. Moreover, patients with <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=qg0Cw2&anker=Z45c7ff4091f4118f9a1659cdec6c8bdd\" data-learningcard-id=\"qg0Cw2\" data-anker=\"Z45c7ff4091f4118f9a1659cdec6c8bdd\" data-sememe-id=\"T406iT\">nephrolithiasis</a> commonly present with a history of intermittent, colicky flank <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=xN0EWg&anker=Zd673a3f7ee36023aab5a267899e984cc\" data-learningcard-id=\"xN0EWg\" data-anker=\"Zd673a3f7ee36023aab5a267899e984cc\" data-section-id=\"NBX-a00\">pain</a> prior to the onset of <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Ni0-7f&anker=Zf87cb8cc29c1c742e9f14924ec88bd7e\" data-learningcard-id=\"Ni0-7f\" data-anker=\"Zf87cb8cc29c1c742e9f14924ec88bd7e\" data-section-id=\"tCaXF5\" data-sememe-id=\"QLYuxp\">hydronephrosis</a>. Finally, the absence of <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Wq0PxS&anker=Z87223b36dc521b28f73a6fa6cb530540\" data-learningcard-id=\"Wq0PxS\" data-anker=\"Z87223b36dc521b28f73a6fa6cb530540\" data-section-id=\"5W1iNf0\" data-sememe-id=\"fg0ku2\">microscopic hematuria</a>, urine crystals, and altered urine <span data-sememe-id=\"Kr1URR0\">pH</span> in this patient make another etiology more likely.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>E) INCORRECT:</h4>\n<a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=pi0Lsf&anker=Z2ded8bd650456858b6477b7b69364ace\" data-learningcard-id=\"pi0Lsf\" data-anker=\"Z2ded8bd650456858b6477b7b69364ace\" data-sememe-id=\"NyY-27\">Benign prostatic hyperplasia</a> (<a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=pi0Lsf&anker=Z2ded8bd650456858b6477b7b69364ace\" data-learningcard-id=\"pi0Lsf\" data-anker=\"Z2ded8bd650456858b6477b7b69364ace\" data-sememe-id=\"NyY-27\">BPH</a>), which is common in older men, can cause <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Ni0-7f&anker=Z8a18451b3b592f9c57f8ef10430c4ef2\" data-learningcard-id=\"Ni0-7f\" data-anker=\"Z8a18451b3b592f9c57f8ef10430c4ef2\" data-section-id=\"HCaKt5\" data-sememe-id=\"mLYVyp\">bladder outlet obstruction</a> and, subsequently, bilateral <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Ni0-7f&anker=Zf87cb8cc29c1c742e9f14924ec88bd7e\" data-learningcard-id=\"Ni0-7f\" data-anker=\"Zf87cb8cc29c1c742e9f14924ec88bd7e\" data-section-id=\"tCaXF5\" data-sememe-id=\"QLYuxp\">hydronephrosis</a>. However, a normal <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=XL09wg&anker=Z5d3564efeb645a3f97c92377b2f3ca28\" data-learningcard-id=\"XL09wg\" data-anker=\"Z5d3564efeb645a3f97c92377b2f3ca28\" data-section-id=\"eccxYY0\" data-sememe-id=\"1LY29p\">digital rectal examination</a> and the absence of <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=pi0Lsf&anker=Ze79ac4d63b09fb8c4842c2ce004cd4e2\" data-learningcard-id=\"pi0Lsf\" data-anker=\"Ze79ac4d63b09fb8c4842c2ce004cd4e2\" data-section-id=\"vBaAcM\" data-sememe-id=\"oYa0JQ\">lower urinary tract symptoms</a> (e.g., <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=kg0mv2&anker=Z4696f8e500da3c30710da62453f005f8\" data-learningcard-id=\"kg0mv2\" data-anker=\"Z4696f8e500da3c30710da62453f005f8\" data-section-id=\"iJXJF_\" data-sememe-id=\"hfbcNG\">urinary frequency</a>, urgency, <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Ku0UH3&anker=Z4f41e78ad20decca22732c8ea55bc4cb\" data-learningcard-id=\"Ku0UH3\" data-anker=\"Z4f41e78ad20decca22732c8ea55bc4cb\" data-sememe-id=\"aT0Q62\">dysuria</a>) make <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=pi0Lsf&anker=Z2ded8bd650456858b6477b7b69364ace\" data-learningcard-id=\"pi0Lsf\" data-anker=\"Z2ded8bd650456858b6477b7b69364ace\" data-sememe-id=\"NyY-27\">BPH</a> unlikely.</div>",
      "hint": "This patient's symptoms of renal failure (fatigue, anorexia, nausea, oliguria, hypertension, peripheral edema) are most likely caused by long-standing bilateral hydronephrosis due to upper urinary tract obstruction (as evidenced by bilateral dilatation of the renal pelvis, calyces, and proximal ureter).",
